1 asso ciation or firm engaged in furnishing lights, heat or power by
2 electricity or natural gas shall have and exercise the right of
3 eminent domain in the same manner and by like proceedings as
4 provided for railroad corporations by laws of this state.
5 B. The power of eminent domain shall not be used for the siting
6 or building of wind turbines energy facilities, solar energy
7 facilities, battery storage facilities, hydrogen gas facilities, or
8 other renewable energy facilities on private property.
9 C. Prior to seeking to exercise eminent domain for an electric
10 transmission facility rated greater than three hundred (300)
11 kilovolts, any person, firm, or corporation under the purview of
12 subsection A of this section must have obtained a Certificate of
13 Authority from the Corporation Commission, as required in Enrolled
14 House Bill No. 2756 of the First Session of the 60th Oklahoma
15 Legislature.
16 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
